@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{frame-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in @code{frame} library with commands for resizing and positioning frames on macOS@. While Emacs can maximize frames natively, it does not provide convenient commands for half-screen layouts---a common arrangement when you want Emacs on one side and another application on the other. This package fills that gap.

The package also includes utilities for restoring the window divider face and returning focus to Emacs from other macOS applications.

The main capabilities are:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Frame sizing.} Commands to maximize the frame or resize it to the left or right half of the screen (@ref{Frame sizing and positioning}).
@item
@strong{Focus and visual restoration.} Restoring focus to Emacs via AppleScript and resetting the window divider face (@ref{Restoration utilities}).
@end itemize

